   Information 10 00174 g001 550
   Figure 1. An illustration of the evaluation procedure. First, the set
   of sequences is split between training and test set. Then, the
   recommender is trained with the sequences available in the training
   set. Finally, the recommender is asked to generate a sequence for each
   seed from the test set; such sequences are compared with the
   corresponding reference sequences.
   Figure 1. An illustration of the evaluation procedure. First, the set
   of sequences is split between training and test set. Then, the
   recommender is trained with the sequences available in the training
   set. Finally, the recommender is asked to generate a sequence for each
   seed from the test set; such sequences are compared with the
   corresponding reference sequences.
